{"article_id":"fzObg0EG68fETWhW","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Did Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein seriously suggest to top Justice Department officials last year","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that someone should secretly tape President Donald Trump ?","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"Or did he make an obviously sarcastic comment","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"that he never intended anyone take seriously ?","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"A new report from the New York Times ' s Adam Goldman and Michael Schmidt says","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"it was the former","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"- and adds","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that Rosenstein also talked about invoking the 25th Amendment","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"to remove Trump from office .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"( Neither ended up happening . )","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"The reporters ' sources are anonymous people","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"\" briefed either on the events themselves or on memos \"","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"written by former deputy FBI director Andrew McCabe and others .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"But a separate report from the Washington Post ' s Devlin Barrett and Matt Zapotosky quotes an anonymous source","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"who was in the room","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"and disputes the account","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"given to the Times .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Per this source ,","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"Rosenstein was rebutting a suggestion by McCabe","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that the Justice Department open an investigation into Trump ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"and said something along the lines of ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"\" What do you want to do , Andy , wire the president ? \"","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"Who ' s right ?","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"The consequences could be enormous .","depth":3},{"id":24,"text":"It was Rosenstein who appointed Mueller as special counsel back in May 2017 ,","depth":5},{"id":25,"text":"and it ' s Rosenstein","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"who continues to oversee Mueller ' s Russia investigation .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Well before these new stories President Trump has privately mused about firing Rosenstein","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"( or Sessions , or Mueller ) ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"so he could put someone","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"he views as more loyal","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"in charge of the Russia probe .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Trump has hesitated on actually following through with this .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"The new Times report , though , will undoubtedly infuriate the president","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"- and could well provide him with the pretext","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"he ' s long sought","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"to justify Rosenstein ' s firing ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"and provoke a showdown over the future of Mueller ' s probe .","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"And in the moments","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"after the Times published it ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"speculation about a new Saturday Night Massacre once again arose in Washington .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Rosenstein was sworn in as deputy attorney general toward the end of April 2017 .","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"Just two weeks later , on May 8 , he and Attorney General Jeff Sessions met in the White House with President Trump","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"to discuss the potential firing of FBI Director James Comey .","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"Afterward , Rosenstein wrote a memo","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"criticizing Comey ' s handling of the Hillary Clinton email investigation ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"which the White House then released the next day","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"to justify Comey ' s firing .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"In the new Times report , Goldman and Schmidt purport to describe Rosenstein ' s behavior and interactions with top Justice Department officials in the week or so after the firing","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"( when ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"it should be noted ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"President Trump himself was behaving quite erratically","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"- seeming to admit on television","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"that he fired Comey over the Russia probe ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"and disclosing classified information to Russians in the Oval Office ) .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"For their two most controversial bits , the Times team doesn ' t seem to be quoting sources with firsthand knowledge .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"Instead , they attribute the report to \" several people \"","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"who \" were briefed either on the events themselves or on memos","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"written by FBI officials \"","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"including McCabe .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"First is Rosenstein ' s supposed comment","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"about recording Trump .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"The Times says","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"it was made during a meeting with McCabe and \" at least four other senior Justice Department officials , \"","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"and describes it as follows :","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Mr. Rosenstein then raised the idea","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"of wearing a recording device or \" wire , \"","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"as he put it ,","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"to secretly tape the president","depth":15},{"id":69,"text":"when he visited the White House .","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"One participant asked","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"whether Mr. Rosenstein was serious ,","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"and he replied animatedly","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"that he was .","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"If not him ,","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"then Mr. McCabe or other F.B.I . officials","depth":15},{"id":76,"text":"interviewing with Mr. Trump for the job","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"could perhaps wear a wire or otherwise record the president ,","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"Mr. Rosenstein offered .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"White House officials never checked his phone","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"when he arrived for meetings there ,","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"Mr. Rosenstein added ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"implying","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"it would be easy to secretly record Mr. Trump .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"But the Times sources were not in the room ,","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"and it ' s not even clear","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"they ' ve seen the memos in question .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"Meanwhile , both the Washington Post and Huffington Post are quoting an anonymous source","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"who was in the room ,","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"claiming","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"the comment was obviously sarcastic .","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"In the Washington Post source ' s account ,","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"Rosenstein was rebutting a suggestion by McCabe","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"that the Justice Department open an investigation into Trump ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"and said something along the lines of ,","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"\" What do you want to do , Andy , wire the president ? \"","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"The Huffington Post also quoted a source","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"present at the meeting","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"( perhaps the same one , perhaps not ) .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"\" I remember this meeting","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"and remember the wire comment , \"","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"the person said .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"\" The statement was sarcastic","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"and was never discussed with any intention","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"of recording a conversation with the president. \"","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"( In any case , there ' s no evidence","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"it was ever carried out ) .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"The Times ' second controversial claim is that Rosenstein discussed using the 25th Amendment","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"to remove Trump from office .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Section 4 of the 25th Amendment of the Constitution states","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"if the vice president and a majority of Cabinet secretaries decide","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"the president is \" unable to discharge the powers and duties \" of the presidency ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"they can start a process","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"that could remove him from office .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"It has never been invoked .","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"According to Goldman and Schmidt ,","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"Rosenstein brought this up in conversations with McCabe and others ,","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"and told McCabe","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"that he might be able to persuade Sessions and then-Homeland Security Secretary John Kelly ,","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"who is now Trump ' s chief of staff ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"to get the process rolling .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"However , the Times report is unclear about when the 25th Amendment comment was purportedly made ,","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"only seeming to attribute it to something","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"Rosenstein said to McCabe ,","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"and that McCabe then repeated to others .","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"\" Based on my personal dealings with the president ,","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"there is no basis","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"to invoke the 25th Amendment , \"","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"Rosenstein said in a statement to the Times .","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"From one perspective , this is a story about two things","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"that didn ' t happen :","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"If the story is accurate ,","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"Rosenstein floated two remarkable possibilities during a tumultuous time 16 months ago ,","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"but neither appears to have actually come to pass .","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"But the near-term consequences are likely to come from the fallout from the story itself , with big implications for Rosenstein ' s future and the future of the Mueller investigation .","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"Since Rosenstein first appointed Mueller in May 2017 ,","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"Washington has awaited the next showdown between President Trump and his Justice Department .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"The president raged privately about potentially firing Mueller as early as June 2017 ,","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"and at various points since has reportedly discussed firing Sessions or Rosenstein too .","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"However , Trump has shied away from actually doing so -","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"evidently realizing","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"that he had no defensible justification ,","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"and fearing the political backlash","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"that would ensue .","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"Trump ' s conservative allies in the House of Representatives have also harshly criticized Rosenstein for months","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"and discussed the prospect","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"of impeaching him with only the thinnest of pretexts .","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"But they basically had nothing ,","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"so the effort was shelved .","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"Now this new story seems so perfectly designed","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"to justify Rosenstein ' s firing","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"that Twitter soon brimmed with suspicion","depth":10},{"id":153,"text":"that the Times ' s sources were trying to bring about that very outcome .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"If you want to question a story","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"without your own information ,","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"but based on your emotions ,","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"and slander a tremendous current NYT reporter in the process ,","depth":12},{"id":158,"text":"that ' s your right .","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"https : //t.co/Fa3Pi0m4","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"De - Maggie Haberman","depth":12},{"id":161,"text":"( @ maggieNYT )","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"September 21 , 2018","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"In any case , Trump does now have something on Rosenstein .","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"He may well calculate","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"that he can portray this behavior as outrageous or insubordinate enough","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"to justify firing the deputy attorney general at long last .","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"And if so ,","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"the crisis over the Russia probe and the rule of law will have finally arrived .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":337,"left":209,"right":336,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":209,"left":191,"right":208,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":178,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":172,"right":177,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":172,"left":170,"right":171,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":170,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":171,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":173,"right":176,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":175,"right":9,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":6,"right":174,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":174,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":180,"right":189,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":180,"left":10,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":11